The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Ahmedabad, Oct. 8 (PTI): The US consulate today advised students seeking American study visa to directly approach it instead of taking the help of agents.          
	Lisa Larson, the vice-counsellor of the US consulate in Mumbai, said agents charge high fees from students.                   
	 Lucknow: Uttar Pradesh police will reopen investigations into the disappearance of a Japanese student, Kota Shinozaki, from an Agra hotel in 2006 after requests from his mother and sister, who are currently on a visit to Lucknow.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Central Board of Direct Taxes has ruled that a person will have to pay a tax on any gift-in-kind exceeding Rs 50,000 unless he furnishes an affidavit affirming he received it from a relative.                  
	 Amravati (PTI): The Congress on Thursday expelled former Maharashtra minister Sunil Deshmukh for six years. Deshmukh is contesting as an Independent from his seat Amravati after the Congress gave the ticket to President Pratibha Patils son Rajendra Shekhawat.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Centre has announced a package to help state governments implement the Sixth Pay Commission pay structure for teachers in degree technical colleges. The Centre will provide partial financial assistance to only those states that implement the revised pay structure.                  
	 Behrampore: Purnima Das, who resigned as the CPM sabhadhipati of the Murshidabad zilla parishad on Thursday, had signed a notification postponing a vote of no-confidence a day before she stepped down. The Congress had brought a no-confidence motion against the Left-run body in which the CPM has only one seat more than the Congress.                                                                                                                           
